featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
The word masjid literally means prostration. It is an Arabic word. Near Ahle Islam, there is the mosque, the building where prayers are offered. The house of Prophet Muhammad (Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam) is considered to be the first mosque.
The word Masjid has also appeared in the Quran, as in the context of Masjid-Haram, this word has been used in countless verses. Some scholars believe that all mosques are actually examples of the Masjid Haram.
